This successful restaurant is already a favorite uptown, amongst local clientele,
wine lovers and serious foodies alike. The location features an expansive
brass bar alongside with traditional Tuscan design elements of the Felice
brand are visible in Robert McKinley’s design details including custom made
tables and leather bench seats. The menu inspired by rustic Tuscan cuisine,

Felice offers a unique wine list composed of over 100 bottles of white, red
and sparkling Italian wines with over 30 offered by the glass. This location
accommodates 55-seats in the restaurant area; the upstairs wine lounge, La
Soffitta, accommodates an additional 35-seats, available for private events.
